treatment.paragraph:
Mouth inferior, lips fleshy, fimbriated, continuous at angle of mouth. Oral teeth villiform, in irregular rows on all tooth-bearing surfaces. Premaxillary tooth band rounded, with 5–6 rows of teeth. Vomerine tooth band continuous with four rows of teeth in middle, anteriorly convex, tapering posterolaterally; its lateral extent exceeds lateral extent of premaxillary. Dentary tooth band separated in middle, broader than premaxillary and vomerine at symphysis, postero-laterally tapering, reaching angle of mouth. Anterior nostril tubular. Gill membranes separated, free from isthmus, not overlapping. Gill opening wide, extending from post-temporal to beyond isthmus. Gill rakers short with 1+3=4 (1) or 1+4=5 (1) or 2+3= 5 (2) rakers on first branchial arch (
Fig. 2
).
